value.0: "Oh look, it is our friend, come back..."
"... to visit us. How can we help you..."
"... today, kind <sir/madam>?"
Two identical female elves stand here amidst a caravan that seems to have escaped the invading army's notice. One begins, "Good day to you..."
Then the other finishes, "stranger. Would you be interested in purchasing some of our goods? Most are in perfect condition..."
"...though there might be some smoke damage. What do you say?"
"Be careful, good <sir/madam>. There are many dangerous creatures..."
"... in this hilly land."
"We have a variety of goods brought..."
"...all the way from the civilized southern cities. Have a look."
"We are always happy..."
"... to answer any questions a customer might have."
"Would you like to purchase some..."
"... of our goods, kind <sir/madam>?"
"I think we should be all right, as long as..."
"... those monsters don't come back. Thank you for..."
"... asking, though."
"Our goods are always welcome here..."
"... since many people in the north think of the south as the only place to get real *civilized* goods. We have done a brisk trade..."
"... with our dyes and exotic materials. But I think now we will have to wait..."
"... until the invaders are stopped, before continuing on to the keep."
They both giggle. "It's just something we started when we were..."
"... just children. Our parents hated it, but after doing it for years..."
"... they got used to it and so did we."
"I am well versed in the magical arts, and we were able to make our entire caravan invisible when..."
"...I was scouting and saw the routed army fleeing the keep."
"Oh, we have never heard that one before..."
"... you are a witty one."
"We are not that powerful and without solid walls to retreat behind..."
"... we would have been easy prey. Better to just be invisible."
"Did you have other questions..."
"... for us, kind <sir/madam>?"
"Yes, there would be little else these sweet elves could have done. Now which of you lasses was Alexis again?"
"I'm Alexis, and you certainly are..."
"... the most handsome dwarf we've ever met. Besides, I am Alexis."
"I don't suppose it matters. You both be fine looking lasses."
"Too bad we are both promised to be married..."
"... to very wealthy elven lords, alas."
"No, I just keep a number of scrolls around with globe of invisibilty spells on them..."
"... for just such an occassion."
"I am Alenor Kinthalis, merchant wizard, and this is my sister..."
"Alexis Kinthalis, merchant and scout. We own this modest enterprise you see here."
"Goodbye."
"What do you have for sale?"
"I have some questions for you."
"That's all my questions."
"Do you need any help?"
"What brought you this far north?"
"Why do you finish each other's sentences?"
"How did you avoid the monsters that attacked the keep?"
"I guess two heads are better than one."
"So why didn't you help, instead of just hiding?"
"That's a powerful spell."
"Back to my other questions."
"Who are you?"
